# UI Structure and Styling

The application uses a minimal console-style theme with clean lines, focusing on a simple and efficient user experience.

## Layout Structure

```
container
├── header
│   ├── h1 (title)
│   ├── repo-input
│   │   ├── input (repo URL)
│   │   └── button (load repo)
│   └── status
└── main
    ├── terminal
    │   ├── terminal-output
    │   └── terminal-input
    └── preview
        └── iframe
```

## Key UI Components

### Header Section

- Title and repository input form
- Status message area showing current operation

### Terminal Section

- Command output area with scrolling
- Command input with prompt

### Preview Section

- iframe for displaying the running application
- Initially shows loading.html while WebContainer initializes

## Styling Highlights

### Color Scheme

- Dark background (`#1e1e1e`) for a modern console look
- Light text (`#d4d4d4`) for readability
- Accent color (`#0078d4`) for buttons and highlights
- Error color (`#e74c3c`) for error messages

### Font Selection

- Monospace fonts for a terminal-like appearance
- Consistent styling across all UI elements

### Layout

- Grid-based layout for clean alignment
- Responsive design with appropriate spacing
- Efficient use of screen space

See [src/style.css](mdc:test-web/src/style.css) for the complete styling implementation.
